1 Random Sample

library(rmap)
data(random_sample_example)
xxx = random_sample_example
head(xxx)
##   e    t      r
## 1 2 5.40 0.5055
## 2 2 0.30 0.6004
## 3 0 2.43 0.4809
## 4 0 0.74 0.7456
## 5 1 2.88 0.6170
## 6 0 0.66 0.4827
e = xxx$e
t = xxx$t
r = xxx$r
t_star = 10
design = "random_sample"
epsilon = length(e)^(-1/3)
N_bootstraps = 100
set.seed(1)
individual = rmap_individual(e, t, r, t_star, design, epsilon, N_bootstraps)
pretty_individual_risk_plot(individual)

2 Two-stage sample

library(rmap)
data(two_stage_sample_example)
xxx = two_stage_sample_example
head(xxx)
##   e    t      r category
## 1 1 1.33 0.4662        A
## 2 1 0.95 0.5449        A
## 3 1 1.00 0.6090        A
## 4 2 2.50 0.6018        B
## 5 1 5.05 0.5827        A
## 6 1 9.44 0.5891        A
e = xxx$e
t = xxx$t
r = xxx$r
t_star = 10
N_first_stage = c(A = 132, B = 168)
N_first_stage
##   A   B 
## 132 168
category = xxx$category
design = list(N_first_stage = N_first_stage, category = category)
epsilon = length(e)^(-1/3)
N_bootstraps = 100
set.seed(2)
individual = rmap_individual(e, t, r, t_star, design, epsilon, N_bootstraps)
pretty_individual_risk_plot(individual)

3 Weighted

library(rmap)
data(weighted_example_cohort_sample)
xxx = weighted_example_cohort_sample
head(xxx)
##   e    t      r category
## 1 1 2.86 0.8517        C
## 2 2 0.96 0.5130        C
## 3 1 2.03 0.5482        C
## 4 1 0.54 0.3027        A
## 5 1 1.94 0.2500        A
## 6 1 2.63 0.7006        D
e = xxx$e
t = xxx$t
r = xxx$r
t_star = 10
data(weighted_example_target_sample)
head(weighted_example_target_sample)
##     x_1   x_2 category
## 1 -3.17  0.15        A
## 2 -1.39  0.85        D
## 3 -3.50 -0.61        A
## 4 -2.44 -0.19        C
## 5 -1.13  0.84        D
## 6 -2.98 -0.03        A
target_category = weighted_example_target_sample$category
category = xxx$category
design = list(target_category = target_category, category = category)
cutoffs = c(0, 0.20, 1)
epsilon = length(e)^(-1/3)
N_bootstraps = 100
set.seed(3)
individual = rmap_individual(e, t, r, t_star, design, epsilon, N_bootstraps)
pretty_individual_risk_plot(individual)
